title: Ukraine: new government led by Yuliia Svyrydenko | OSW Centre for Eastern Studies
snippet: In December 2020, she became deputy to Andrii Yermak, head of the Office of the President of Ukraine, with responsibility for economic policy. From November 2021, she served as First Deputy Prime Minister and Minister of Economy in Denys Shmyhal’s government. In 2025, she led negotiations with the United States on the terms of the raw materials agreement.
